---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout title="About — Maai & AI">
  <div class="about">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        I'm Maaike. I work at the intersection of conversation design, voice
        interfaces, and AI. This is my digital garden: a non-linear, associative
        collection of ideas, notes, articles, and projects at various stages of
        growth.
      </p>
      <p>
        Unlike a blog, nothing here is sorted by date. Ideas link to each other,
        evolve over time, and sometimes get composted when they've run their
        course. If you're used to scrolling a feed, this might feel different.
        Try clicking something that catches your eye and see where it takes you.
      </p>

      <h2>What grows here</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Articles</strong> — longer thinking pieces, often migrated from Substack or written here</li>
        <li><strong>Field notes</strong> — observations and reflections from working with AI</li>
        <li><strong>Seeds</strong> — ideas waiting to germinate</li>
        <li><strong>Experiments</strong> — hands-on explorations you can try yourself</li>
        <li><strong>Videos</strong> — talks, tutorials, and recordings</li>
        <li><strong>Library</strong> — books I've read, am reading, or want to read</li>
        <li><strong>Weblinks</strong> — commentary on external content</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How maturity works</h2>
      <p>Each piece has a maturity indicator showing how developed it is:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>🌱 <strong>Seedling</strong> — just getting started</li>
        <li>🌿 <strong>Sprout</strong> — taking shape, being worked out</li>
        <li>🪴 <strong>Plant</strong> — solid, well-formed</li>
        <li>🌳 <strong>Tree</strong> — finished, stable</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Connections</h2>
      <p>
        Content is cross-linked with wiki-links. You'll see backlinks at the
        bottom of posts, related items in the sidebar, and suggested reading from
        the library. The <a href="/explore">explore page</a> is an interactive
        map of everything in the garden, organized into territories by topic.
      </p>

      <h2>AI transparency</h2>
      <p>Some content here is generated with AI assistance. Every piece carries an indicator:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>100% Maai</strong> — fully written by me, no AI</li>
        <li><strong>Assisted</strong> — my ideas and structure, AI helped refine</li>
        <li><strong>Co-created</strong> — generated by AI based on my ideas and direction</li>
        <li><strong>Generated</strong> — fully AI-generated, reviewed by me</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Projects</h2>
      <p>
        Larger threads of work are organized as projects, each with a hub page
        and related files. You can find them on the
        <a href="/projects">projects page</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: var(--content-width);
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  .about h1 {
    margin-block-end: var(--space-xl);
  }
</style>
